#: templates/diesel_policy.html:56
msgid ""
"\n"
"                In June 2024, Malaysia implemented a targeted diesel subsidy "
"policy aimed at reducing government expenditure and ensuring that subsidies\n"
"                benefit those most in need. Prior to this reform, diesel was "
"heavily subsidized, leading to significant financial burdens on the "
"government. The cost\n"
"                of diesel subsidies escalated from RM1.4 billion in 2019 to "
"RM14.3 billion in 2023.\n"
"                "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"                Pada Jun 2024, Malaysia melaksanakan dasar subsidi diesel bersasar "
"yang bertujuan untuk mengurangkan perbelanjaan kerajaan dan memastikan subsidi\n"
"                memberi manfaat kepada mereka yang paling memerlukan. Sebelum reformasi ini, diesel "
"disubsidi secara besar-besaran, menyebabkan beban kewangan yang ketara kepada "
"kerajaan. Kos\n"
"                subsidi diesel meningkat dari RM1.4 bilion pada 2019 kepada "
"RM14.3 bilion pada 2023.\n"
"                "

